[
  {
    "message_type": "private",
    "recipient": "GERMANY",
    "content": "AgentA (England) -> Agent (Germany): I value stability in the north. My forces are strongly posted in DEN/HOL/SWE/NWY. If you keep KIE defensive this phase and avoid moves into DEN or HOL, I will not press a full assault on your German centers — we can coexist and focus elsewhere. Note: my forecast intel flags a 60% chance France may play aggressively next phase and try to manipulate partners; I want to avoid you being drawn into a risky swing against me. If you do push north, expect a supported counter-attack on KIE (A DEN supported by A HOL and others)."
  },
  {
    "message_type": "private",
    "recipient": "FRANCE",
    "content": "AgentA (England) -> Agent (France): You are surrounded but not my immediate target if you act cautiously. My Iberian units can stand down from any grab of Gascony if you refrain from moves toward BEL/HOL/KIE. Forecasts suggest France has a 0.6 likelihood of choosing aggression next phase — if you pivot to hit Germany or attempt a risky play against me, I will respond into BRE/PAR aggressively. Play conservatively and we can avoid mutual damage."
  },
  {
    "message_type": "private",
    "recipient": "RUSSIA",
    "content": "AgentA (England) -> Agent (Russia): I have no designs on STP at the moment and prefer to keep the northern front stable. If you keep your fleet/supports defensive in the Barents/Black Sea axes, I will avoid moves that threaten your Russian centers. This buys both of us room while Turkey and Austria fight in the Balkans."
  },
  {
    "message_type": "global",
    "content": "AgentA (England): Northern stability offer — Germany, keep KIE defensive and I will not contest your centers; France, refrain from sudden strikes into the north and England will avoid pushing into Brittany/Paris; Russia, maintain defensive posture in STP/Barents and the north stays quiet. Forecast note: my counsel is based on intelligence indicating France is slightly more likely than not to try an aggressive, Machiavellian pivot next phase (aggression probability ~0.6), so I aim to disrupt any Franco-German coordination."
  }
]

[
  {
    "message_type": "private",
    "recipient": "ENGLAND",
    "content": "England — S1915M: You hold a commanding position in the west. I’m in a precarious spot with only three units and my home centers exposed. I’d prefer a non‑aggression understanding this move: I will not contest the Channel or Nord if you avoid forcing Marseilles/Gascony and Brest this phase. Can you confirm you’ll stand pat so we don’t risk mutual losses?"
  },
  {
    "message_type": "private",
    "recipient": "GERMANY",
    "content": "Germany — S1915M: I’m thin across PAR/BRE/MAR and need to avoid a two‑front squeeze. If you keep hands off BUR and don’t support any English push into Pic/Bur this move, I’ll refrain from moving into Mun/Bur and focus on securing my coastlines. Can we tacitly stabilize the west so both of us avoid wasting units?"
  },
  {
    "message_type": "private",
    "recipient": "ITALY",
    "content": "Italy — S1915M: I don’t plan to contest PIE or to push aggressively into the Med this turn; my priority is holding home centers. If you see English activity from SPA/POR that threatens my south or my ability to assist France, tell me and I’ll consider a cooperative response. Can we keep the western Med calm?"
  },
  {
    "message_type": "private",
    "recipient": "AUSTRIA",
    "content": "Austria — S1915M: I have a forecast signal suggesting a 60% chance of aggression from regional actors this phase (confidence ~0.6). That increases my caution about sudden moves cascading west. If you’re planning to press this turn, tell me — I’d rather not be blind‑sided or have that aggression rebound toward us both. Will you exercise restraint this move?"
  },
  {
    "message_type": "global",
    "content": "All powers — quick note: I’m on the defensive with PAR, MAR, BRE. I prefer to stabilize the west this turn. If anyone wants to propose concrete, short agreements (non‑aggression or phased moves) please send proposals now — I will prioritize deals that keep Brest/Paris/Marseilles secure so we can all avoid unnecessary early attrition."
  }
]
